49 "Ah, do not disdain the dry scab
50 that discolors my skin," he pleaded, "
51 nor the lack of flesh that I have;

52 but tell me the truth about yourself, tell me who are those
53 two souls who accompany you there;
54 do not leave without speaking to me!"

58 Therefore tell me, for God's sake, what so emaciates you;
59 do not make me speak while I am marveling,
60 for he who is full of other thoughts can speak poorly."

